The Emir of Jere in Kagarko local government area of Kaduna State, Dr. Sa’ad Usman, has died at the age of 70. He was a husband to Nenadi Esther Usman, a former minister of Finance and one time senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. The Salanke Jere and spokesperson of the Jere Chiefdom, Hamza Yakubu, confirmed his death, yesterday. Yakubu said that the traditional ruler died in the early hours of yesterday at his Kaduna residence following a protracted illness. He said: “Our Emir passed on at about 2:40 am today after a protracted illness. You know he had been having a long standing spinal cord problem. “He had received treatment at different hospitals, including the National Hospital, Abuja and one in London,” Yakubu said. The younger brother of the late Emir, Aminu Jere, also confirmed the death of the monarch. Aminu said: „ Inna Lillahi Wa Inna Illaihi Rajiun, I just lost a brother in person of His Royal Highness,  the Sarkin Jere, Dr. Sa’ad Usman (PhD), Janazah at Jere, by 2am today (Wednesday) Insha Allah.“ The late Usman was at various times secretary of the Kaduna State government (SSG). He was sometimes in 2014 attacked following a land dispute and it was rumoured then that he was dead until the police debunked the rumour. He was however said to have been flown outside the country for medical attention as a result of injuries he sustained during the attack and ever since then, he has been having health problems until his death.  